---
import PageLayout from "@layouts/PageLayout.astro"
import Container from "@components/Container.astro"

const pageTitle = "Rights and Permissions"
const pageDescription =
  "How Canon & Compass handles copyright, reuse permissions, software licensing, and brand protection."
---

<PageLayout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <section class="bg-white py-24 text-ink dark:bg-black dark:text-white">
    <Container size="md">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">
          Rights
        </p>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-serif font-bold tracking-tight md:text-4xl">
          Rights and permissions
        </h1>
        <p class="text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          Canon &amp; Compass is a public website and a public code repository, but those are not the same
          thing as a blanket permission to reuse everything in it.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          This page clarifies what may be reused, what remains reserved, and how to ask permission when you
          want to quote, republish, adapt, or share material from this project.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-stone-50 py-20 text-ink dark:bg-zinc-900 dark:text-white">
    <Container size="md">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold tracking-tight md:text-3xl">Software and code</h2>
        <p class="text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          Unless otherwise noted, the software and site infrastructure in this repository are licensed under
          the MIT License. That applies to the code used to build and run the site, not automatically to the
          editorial content published through it.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          The software terms are described in the repository&apos;s <code>LICENSE</code> file.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white py-20 text-ink dark:bg-black dark:text-white">
    <Container size="md">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold tracking-tight md:text-3xl">Path-level rights map</h2>
        <p class="text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          Canon &amp; Compass uses a mixed-rights structure because the repository contains both software and
          original editorial work.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-4 text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          <li><strong class="text-ink dark:text-white">Reserved content:</strong> all MDX and frontmatter in <code>src/content/**</code>.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink dark:text-white">Reserved brand assets:</strong> <code>public/brand.svg</code>, <code>public/canonandcompass.jpg</code>, <code>public/favicon.svg</code>, and <code>public/favicon_black.svg</code>.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink dark:text-white">Mixed files:</strong> some source files contain both MIT-covered implementation code and reserved Canon &amp; Compass prose such as headings, descriptions, and calls to action.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink dark:text-white">Separately noticed assets:</strong> some files may carry their own upstream or embedded notices, which continue to apply.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white py-20 text-ink dark:bg-black dark:text-white">
    <Container size="md">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold tracking-tight md:text-3xl">Editorial content and assets</h2>
        <p class="text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          Unless otherwise noted, the written content, MDX entries, original site copy, graphics, and brand
          assets on Canon &amp; Compass are all rights reserved.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-4 text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          <li><strong class="text-ink dark:text-white">You may not</strong> republish full articles, mirror the site, create derivative versions for distribution, sell the content, or use it for model training without prior written permission, except where applicable law allows otherwise.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink dark:text-white">You may quote limited excerpts</strong> for review, commentary, teaching, or similar lawful uses when the quotation is properly attributed and not misleadingly edited.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink dark:text-white">You may not use the name or branding</strong> in a way that suggests affiliation, endorsement, or official partnership without permission.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-stone-50 py-20 text-ink dark:bg-zinc-900 dark:text-white">
    <Container size="md">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold tracking-tight md:text-3xl">Permissions</h2>
        <p class="text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          For republication, curriculum use, translation, adaptation, licensing, or any broader reuse request,
          email <a href="mailto:contact@canonandcompass.com" class="underline underline-offset-4 decoration-black/30 hover:decoration-current dark:decoration-white/30">contact@canonandcompass.com</a>.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          Include the material you want to use, where you plan to use it, whether the use is commercial or
          noncommercial, and whether you want an excerpt, full text, or adaptation.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white py-20 text-ink dark:bg-black dark:text-white">
    <Container size="md">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold tracking-tight md:text-3xl">Reporting unauthorized copies</h2>
        <p class="text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          If Canon &amp; Compass content is reposted without permission, preserve the URL, screenshots, and
          publication dates first. Then use the hosting platform&apos;s copyright or DMCA reporting process and
          point back to the original Canon &amp; Compass publication where possible.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          This page is a practical rights notice, not legal advice.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
